<p style=3D"text-align: justify;" class=3D"style119" align=3D"justify"><spa=
n style=3D"font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">TUV Rheinland (India) Pvt. =
Ltd. is conducting the ISO 9001:2015 Lead Auditor Course from 22 &ndash; 26=
 August 2016 in New Delhi. This is a five-day interactive training course, =
intended for qualifying individuals as Lead Auditors. Our Lead Auditor Cour=
ses are registered with International Registrar of Certified Auditors (IRCA=
). The course fulfills the requirements for qualifying as Auditors/Lead Aud=
itors to the IRCA Scheme. This course provides valuable inputs on Quality M=
anagement System and provides practical skills essential to become a compet=
ent lead auditor. By the end of this course, delegates will be able to perf=
orm first, second and third party audits of quality management systems agai=
nst ISO 9001:2015, in accordance with ISO 19011 and ISO 17021 as applicable=
.</span></p>
<p class=3D"style119" align=3D"left"><span style=3D"font-size: x-small; col=
or: #000000;">Benefits:</span></p>
<p class=3D"style119" align=3D"left"><span style=3D"font-size: x-small; col=
or: #000000;">Upon successful completion of the course you should be able t=
o:</span></p>
<div class=3D"style97" align=3D"left">
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">D=
escribe the purpose of a quality management system (QMS)</span></li>
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">E=
xplain the high level structure</span></li>
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">E=
xplain the risk based approach</span></li>
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">E=
xplain the purpose, content and interrelationship of ISO 9000:2015, ISO 190=
11:2011, and ISO 17021:2011</span></li>
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">I=
nterpret the requirements of ISO 9001:2015 within the context of audit</spa=
n></li>
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">D=
escribe the roles and responsibilities of auditors and lead auditors</span>=
</li>
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">P=
lan and conduct an audit in accordance with ISO 19011 and ISO 17021 and dem=
onstrate the ability to:</span>
<ul>
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-seri=
f; font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">Plan and prepare effectively</span>=
</li>
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-seri=
f; font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">Gather objective evidence, through =
effective interviewing, observation, sampling and note taking.</span></li>
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-seri=
f; font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">Analyse and interpret information i=
n order to determine conformance with requirements.</span></li>
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-seri=
f; font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">Report the audit, including writing=
 valid, factual and value-adding non-conformity report.</span></li>
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-family: arial,helvetica,sans-seri=
f; font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">Undertake audit follow-up activitie=
s, including evaluating the effectiveness of corrective action.</span></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<p class=3D"style119" align=3D"left"><span style=3D"font-size: x-small; col=
or: #000000;">Outline:</span></p>
<div class=3D"style97" align=3D"left">
<ul type=3D"disc">
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">K=
nowledge of standards</span></li>
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">K=
nowledge of the audit processes and responsibilities</span></li>
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">K=
nowledge of how to plan an audit</span></li>
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">K=
nowledge of how to carry out the audit</span></li>
<li class=3D"style95"><span style=3D"font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">K=
nowledge of how to report the audit findings and carry out the follow up ac=
tivities</span></li>
</ul>
</div>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;" class=3D"style119" align=3D"justify"><spa=
n style=3D"font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">Participants Profile: The c=
ourse would benefit personnel from Quality, Inspection, Maintenance, Purcha=
se, Production, Marketing, Sales and Auditors (External & Internal), manage=
ment representatives, supervisors, Personnel with industrial / Institutiona=
l experience etc.</span></p>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;" class=3D"style119" align=3D"justify"><spa=
n style=3D"font-size: x-small; color: #000000;">Examination: There would be=
 a written examination at the end of this course. Delegates who successfull=
y complete both the examination and the continuous assessment will be award=
ed a Certificate of Successful Completion and will satisfy the formal train=
ing requirements for IRCA QMS Auditor Certification scheme.</span></p>
<p style=3D"text-align: justify;" class=3D"style95" align=3D"justify"><span=
